<body>

  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="title">Paneer Tikka</h1>
    <img src="/images/paneer.png" alt="" class="hero-img">

    <div class="section">
      <p style="text-align: center;"><em>Paneer Tikka is a flavorful Indian appetizer made with marinated paneer cubes grilled to smoky perfection with bell peppers and onions.</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Ingredients</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>200g paneer (cut into cubes)</li>
        <li>1/2 cup thick curd/yogurt</li>
        <li>1 tbsp gram flour (besan)</li>
        <li>1 tsp ginger-garlic paste</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp red chilli powder</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp garam masala<li>
        <li>1/2 tsp chaat masala</li>
        <li>1 tbsp lemon juice and 1 tbsp oil</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Method</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>In a bowl, mix curd, besan, ginger-garlic paste, turmeric, red chilli powder, garam masala, chaat masala, lemon juice, oil, and salt.</li>
        <li>Add paneer cubes, onion, and capsicum to the marinade. Mix gently and coat well. Let it rest for at least 30 minutes.</li>
        <li>Tawa Method: Heat a little oil on a non-stick tawa/pan and cook the marinated pieces on medium heat till golden and slightly charred.</li>
        <li>Oven Method: Preheat to 200°C. Place paneer and veggies on skewers and bake for 15–20 minutes, flipping once in between.</li>
        <li>Garnish with lemon wedges and onion rings. Sprinkle chaat masala on top for extra zing.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
